#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:20
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrading &sle;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:23
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&slereg; (&slea;) allows to update an existing system to the new version, "
"for example, going from &slea; 11 SP4 to &slea; 12. No new installation is "
"needed. Existing data, such as home and data directories and system "
"configuration, is kept intact. You can update from a local CD or DVD drive "
"or from a central network installation source."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:31
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This chapter explains how to manually upgrade your &sle; system, be it by "
"DVD, network, an automated process, or &susemgr;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: dm:translation
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:37
#, no-c-format
msgid "<dm:translation>yes</dm:translation>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:41
#, no-c-format
msgid "General Preparations"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:43
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Before starting the update procedure, make sure your system is properly "
"prepared. Among others, preparation involves backing up data and checking "
"the release notes."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:50
#, no-c-format
msgid "Temporarily Disable Kernel Multiversion Support"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:51
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&productname; allows to install multiple Kernel versions by enabling the "
"respective settings in <filename>/etc/zypp/zypp.conf</filename>. Support for "
"this feature needs to be temporarily disabled for updating to a service "
"pack. When the update has successfully finished; multiversion support can be "
"re-enabled again. To disable multiversion support, comment the respective "
"lines in <filename>/etc/zypp/zypp.conf</filename>. The result should look "
"like this:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:60
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"#multiversion = provides:multiversion(kernel)\n"
"#multiversion.kernels = latest,running"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:61
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To re-activate this feature after a successful update, remove the comment "
"signs. For more information about multiversion support, refer to <xref "
"linkend=\"cha.tuning.multikernel.enable\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:69
#, no-c-format
msgid "Check the Release Notes"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:70
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the release notes you can find additional information on what has changed "
"since the previous release of &sle;. Verify there if your specific hardware "
"or setup needs special considerations, which of your favorite specific "
"software packages have changed significantly, and which precautions you "
"should take in addition to the general recommendations of this section. The "
"release notes also provide last-minute information and known issues that "
"could not make it to the manual on time."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:79
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The current version of the release notes document containing the latest "
"information on &productname; can be read online at <link xlink:href=\"http://"
"www.suse.com/documentation/\"></link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:87
#, no-c-format
msgid "Make a Backup"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:88
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Before updating, copy existing configuration files to a separate medium "
"(such as tape device, removable hard disk, etc.) to back up the data. This "
"primarily applies to files stored in <filename>/etc</filename> and some "
"directories and files in <filename>/var</filename> and <filename>/opt</"
"filename>. You may also want to write the user data in <filename>/home</"
"filename> (the <envar>HOME</envar> directories) to a backup medium. Back up "
"this data as &rootuser;. Only &rootuser; has read permissions for all local "
"files."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:98
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have selected <guimenu>Update an Existing System</guimenu> as the "
"installation mode in &yast;, you can choose to do a (system) backup at a "
"later point in time. You can choose to include all modified files and files "
"from the <filename>/etc/sysconfig</filename> directory. However, this is not "
"a complete backup, as all the other important directories mentioned above "
"are missing. Find the backup in the <filename>/var/adm/backup</filename> "
"directory."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:110
#, no-c-format
msgid "Migrate your MySQL Database"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: remark
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:111
#, no-c-format
msgid "toms 2015-09-03: already reviewed by Ondrej and Krist√Ωna."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:112
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As of &sle; 12, &suse; switched from MySQL to MariaDB. Before you start any "
"upgrade, it is highly recommended to back up your database."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:119 sle_update_upgrading.xml:224
#, no-c-format
msgid "To perform the database migration, do the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:124
#, no-c-format
msgid "Log in to your &sle; 11 machine."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:129
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create a dump file:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:132
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;<command>mysqldump</command> -u root -p --all-databases > "
"mysql_backup.sql"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:133
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By default, <command>mysqldump</command> does not dump the "
"<literal>INFORMATION_SCHEMA</literal> or <literal>performance_schema</"
"literal> database. For more details refer to <link xlink:href=\"https://dev."
"mysql.com/doc/refman/5.5/en/mysqldump.html\"></link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:141
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Store your dump file, the configuration file <filename>/etc/my.cnf</"
"filename>, and the directory <filename>/etc/mysql/</filename> for later "
"investigation (<emphasis>NOT</emphasis> installation!) in a safe place."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:149
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Perform your upgrade. After the upgrade, your former configuration file "
"<filename>/etc/my.cnf</filename> is still intact. You can find the new "
"configuration in the file <filename>/etc/my.cnf.rpmnew</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:156
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Configure your MariaDB database to your needs. Do <emphasis>NOT</emphasis> "
"use the former configuration file and directory, but use it as a reminder "
"and adapt it."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:163
#, no-c-format
msgid "Make sure you start the MariaDB server:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:166
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;<command>systemctl</command> start mysql"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:167
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to start the MariaDB server on every boot, enable the service:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:171
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;<command>systemctl</command> enable mysql"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:176
#, no-c-format
msgid "Verify that MariaDB is running properly by connecting to the database:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:179
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;<command>mysql</command> -u root -p"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:185
#, no-c-format
msgid "Migrate your &postgresql; Database"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: remark
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:186
#, no-c-format
msgid "toms 2015-09-09: FATE#319049"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: remark
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:187
#, no-c-format
msgid "Already reviewd by Reinhard"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:188
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&slea;11 SP3 and &slea;12 GA get a newer version of the &postgresql; "
"database as a maintenance update. Because of the required migration work of "
"the database, there is no automatic upgrade process. As such, the switch "
"from one version to another needs to be done manually."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:194
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The migration process is conducted by the <command>pg_upgrade</command> "
"command which is an alternative method of the classic dump and reload. In "
"comparison with the <quote>dump &amp; reload</quote> method, "
"<command>pg_upgrade</command> makes the migration less time-consuming."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:200
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each &postgresql; version stores its files in different, version-dependent "
"directories. After the update the directories will change to:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:206
#, no-c-format
msgid "&slea;11 SP3/SP4"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:208
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<filename>/usr/lib/postgresql91/</filename> to <filename>/usr/lib/"
"postgresql94/</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:215
#, no-c-format
msgid "&slea;12 GA"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:217
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<filename>/usr/lib/postgresql93/</filename> to <filename>/usr/lib/"
"postgresql94/</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:229
#, no-c-format
msgid "Make sure the following preconditions are fulfilled:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:234
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If not already done, upgrade any package of the old &postgresql; version to "
"the latest release through a maintenance update."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:240
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create a backup of your existing database."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:245
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Install the packages of the new &postgresql; major version. For &slea;12 "
"this means to install <package>postgresql94-server</package> and all the "
"packages it depends on."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:253
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Install the package <package>postgresql94-contrib</package> which contains "
"the command <command>pg_upgrade</command>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:260
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Make sure you have enough free space in your &postgresql; data area, which "
"is <filename>/var/lib/pgsql/data</filename> by default. If space is tight, "
"try to reduce size with the following SQL command on each database (can take "
"very long!):"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:266
#, no-c-format
msgid "VACUUM FULL"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:271
#, no-c-format
msgid "Stop the &postgresql; server:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:274
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;<command>/usr/sbin/rcpostgresql</command> stop"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:277
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rename your old data directory:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:280
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;<command>mv</command> /var/lib/pgsql/data /var/lib/pgsql/data."
"old"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:283
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create a new data directory:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:286
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;<command>mkdir</command> -p /var/lib/pgsql/data"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:289
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have changed your configuration files in the old version, copy the "
"files <filename>postgresql.conf</filename> <filename>pg_hba.conf</filename> "
"to your new <filename>data</filename> directory:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:295
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;<command>cp</command> /var/lib/pgsql/data.old/*.conf \\\n"
"     /var/lib/pgsql/data"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:298
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Initialize your new database instance either manually with <command>initdb</"
"command> or by starting and stopping &postgresql;, which will do it "
"automatically:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:303
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;<command>/usr/sbin/rcpostgresql</command> start\n"
"&prompt.root;<command>/usr/sbin/rcpostgresql</command> stop"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:306
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Start the migration process and replace the <replaceable>OLD</replaceable> "
"placeholder with the older version:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:310
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;<command>pg_upgrade</command> \\\n"
"   --old-datadir \"/var/lib/pgsql/data.old\" \\\n"
"   --new-datadir \"/var/lib/pgsql/data\" \\\n"
"   --old-bindir \"/usr/lib/postgresql<replaceable>OLD</replaceable>/bin/\" "
"\\\n"
"   --new-bindir \"/usr/lib/postgresql94/bin/\""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:313
#, no-c-format
msgid "Start your new database instance:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:316
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;<command>/usr/sbin/rcpostgresql</command> start"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:319
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Check if the migration was successful. There is no general tool to automate "
"this step. It depends on your use case how much and what you want to test."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:326
#, no-c-format
msgid "Remove any old &postgresql; packages and your old data directory:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:329
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;<command>zypper</command> search -s postgresql<replaceable>OLD</"
"replaceable> | xargs zypper rm -u\n"
"&prompt.root;<command>rm</command> -rf /var/lib/pgsql/data.old"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:335
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create Non-MD5 Server Certificates for Java Applications"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: remark
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:336
#, no-c-format
msgid "toms 2016-07-27: from bsc#970153, c#24"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:337
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"During the update from SP1 to SP2, MD5-based certificates were disabled as "
"part of a security fix. If you have certificates created as MD5, recreate "
"your certificates with the following steps:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:345
#, no-c-format
msgid "Open a terminal and log in as &rootuser;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:350
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create a private key:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:353
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;<command>openssl</command> genrsa -out server.key 1024"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:354
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want a stronger key, exchange <literal>1024</literal> with a higher "
"number, for example, <literal>4096</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:360
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create a certificate signing request (CSR):"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:363
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;<command>openssl</command> req -new -key server.key -out server."
"csr"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:366
#, no-c-format
msgid "Self-sign the certificate:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:369
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;<command>openssl</command> x509 -req -days 365 -in <!--\n"
"     -->server.csr -signkey server.key -out server.crt"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:372
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create the PEM file:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:375
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;<command>cat</command> server.key server.crt > server.pem"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:378
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Place the files <filename>server.crt</filename>, <filename>server.csr</"
"filename>, <filename>server.key</filename>, and <filename>server.pem</"
"filename> in the respective directories where the keys can be found. For "
"Tomcat, for example, this directory is <filename>/etc/tomcat/ssl/</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:389
#, no-c-format
msgid "Shut Down Virtual Machine Guests"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:390
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If your machine serves as a &vmhost; for &kvm; or &xen;, make sure to "
"properly shut down all running &vmguest;s prior to the update. Otherwise you "
"may not be able to access the guests after the update."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:398
#, no-c-format
msgid "Check the <command>clientSetup4SMT.sh</command> script on SMT clients"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:399
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you are migrating your client OS that is registered against an &smt; "
"server, you need to check if the version of the <command>clientSetup4SMT.sh</"
"command> script on your host is up to date. <command>clientSetup4SMT.sh</"
"command> from older versions of &smt; cannot manage &smt; 12 clients. If you "
"apply software patches regularly on your SMT server, you can always find the "
"latest version of <command>clientSetup4SMT.sh</command> at <filename>&lt;"
"SMT_HOSTNAME&gt;/repo/tools/clientSetup4SMT.sh</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:409
#, no-c-format
msgid "Disk Space"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:411
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Software tends to <quote>grow</quote> from version to version. Therefore, "
"take a look at the available partition space before updating. If you suspect "
"you are running short of disk space, secure your data before increasing the "
"available space by resizing partitions, for example. There is no general "
"rule regarding how much space each partition should have. Space requirements "
"depend on your particular partitioning profile and the software selected."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:421
#, no-c-format
msgid "Automatic Check for Enough Space in &yast;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:422
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"During the update procedure, &yast; will check the free disk space and "
"display a warning to the user if the installation may exceed the available "
"amount. In that case, performing the update may lead to an "
"<emphasis>unusable system</emphasis>! Only if you know exactly what you are "
"doing (by testing beforehand), you can skip the warning and continue the "
"update."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:433
#, no-c-format
msgid "Checking Disk Space on Non-Btrfs File Systems"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:434
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the <command>df</command> command to list available disk space. For "
"example, in <xref linkend=\"aus.update.df\"/>, the root partition is "
"<filename>/dev/sda3</filename> (mounted as <filename>/</filename>)."
msgstr ""

