#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1154
#, no-c-format
msgid "Retaining Kernel Packages"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: remark
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1156
#, no-c-format
msgid "toms 2015-08-26: bsc#753809"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: remark
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1158
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"toms 2015-08-26: some parts are taken (\"stolen\") from the wiki at https://"
"en.opensuse.org/SDB:Keep_multiple_kernel_versions and adapted"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: primary
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1163
#, no-c-format
msgid "multiversion kernels"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1165
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When installing a new kernel with &yast; or Zypper, &sle; preserves the last "
"two kernels and the running one. Usually this is sufficient."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1170
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"However, there may be situations where you need to preserve more kernel "
"versions, for example, for testing purposes. To enable this, &sle; supports "
"the <emphasis>multiversion kernel feature</emphasis>. By enabling and "
"configuring this feature the default behavior can be changed and configured "
"to:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1180
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"delete an old kernel only after the system has been rebooted successfully "
"with the new kernel"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1186
#, no-c-format
msgid "keep a specified number of older kernels as fallback"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1191
#, no-c-format
msgid "keep a specific kernel version"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1197
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After the successful reboot, a script will compare the list of installed "
"kernels with the settings in <filename>/etc/zypp/zypp.conf</filename> and "
"delete those kernels that are no longer needed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1204
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enabling the Multiversion Kernel Feature"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1205
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The default behavior is defined in the configuration file <filename>/etc/"
"zypp/zypp.conf</filename>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1209
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;<command>grep</command> ^multiversion /etc/zypp/zypp.conf\n"
"multiversion = provides:multiversion(kernel)\n"
"multiversion.kernels = latest,latest-1,running"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1210
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Remove any hash mark (#) before the line <literal>multiversion</literal> "
"above to enable this feature (which should already be the case). The second "
"line is used to configure <emphasis>which</emphasis> kernels need to be "
"preserved. You need to enable both, otherwise the system will keep "
"<emphasis>all</emphasis> kernels and it will fill up your hard disk."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1217
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <literal>multiversion.kernels</literal> line can contain several "
"keywords in different combinations and order:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: option
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1223
#, no-c-format
msgid "latest"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1226
#, no-c-format
msgid "Keep kernel with the highest version number"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: option
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1232
#, no-c-format
msgid "latest-<replaceable>N</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1235
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Keep kernel with the <replaceable>N</replaceable>th highest version number; "
"<replaceable>N</replaceable> is a number starting from 1"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: option
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1242
#, no-c-format
msgid "running"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1245
#, no-c-format
msgid "Keep the current running kernel"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: option
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1251
#, no-c-format
msgid "oldest"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1254
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Keep kernel with the lowest version number (the kernel on the released "
"product)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: option
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1261
#, no-c-format
msgid "oldest-<replaceable>N</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1264
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Keep kernel with the <replaceable>N</replaceable>th lowest version number"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: option
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1271
#, no-c-format
msgid "3.12.28-4.6"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1274
#, no-c-format
msgid "Keep this exact kernel version"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1283
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use Case: Deleting an Old Kernel After Reboot Only"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1284
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You want to make sure that an old kernel will only be deleted after the "
"system has rebooted successfully of the new kernel."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1288 sle_update_upgrading.xml:1309
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1329
#, no-c-format
msgid "Change the following line in <filename>/etc/zypp/zypp.conf</filename>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1291
#, no-c-format
msgid "multiversion.kernels = latest,running"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1292
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The previous parameters tell the system to keep the latest kernel and the "
"running one only if they differ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1299
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use Case: Keeping Older Kernels as Fallback"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1300
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You want to keep one or more kernel versions to have one or more "
"<quote>spare</quote> kernels."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1304
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This use case can be useful if you need kernels for testing reasons. In case "
"something goes wrong, for example, your machine does not boot, you still can "
"use one or more kernel versions which are known to be good."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1312
#, no-c-format
msgid "multiversion.kernels = latest,latest-1,latest-2,running"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1313
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you reboot your system after the installation of a new kernel, the "
"system will keep three kernels: the new and running kernel (configured as "
"<literal>latest,running</literal>), the previous kernel version of the new "
"kernel (configured as <literal>latest-1</literal>), and the predecessor of "
"the previous kernel version (configured as <literal>latest-2</literal>)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1323
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use Case: Keep a Specific Kernel Version"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1324
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You make regular system updates and install new kernel versions. However, "
"you are also compiling your own kernel version for various reasons and want "
"to make sure that the system will keep it."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1332
#, no-c-format
msgid "multiversion.kernels = latest,3.12.28-4.20,running"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_upgrading.xml:1333
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you reboot your system after the installation of a new kernel, the "
"system will keep two kernels: the new and running kernel (configured as "
"<literal>latest,running</literal>) and your self-compiled kernel (configured "
"as <literal>3.12.28-4.20</literal>)."
msgstr ""
